						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up against the front wall of the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>[SADĀ]ŚIVADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>Paridhāvi (1552 A.D.)</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Paridhāvi, Kārttika, śu. 10 and this can be assigned to the period of 16th century on the basis of palaeography and internal evidences. The date of the record may correspond to November 11, Friday 1552 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged, Incomplete and worn-out. Mentions the date in cyclic year and kings name.</p>						

						</summary>
